WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.221 --> 00:00:03.159
_

2
00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:04.720
Hey! Stop!

3
00:00:06.528 --> 00:00:09.910
Somebody stop that kid!
Hey. get back here!

4
00:00:09.923 --> 00:00:11.290
[ Tires screech ]

5
00:00:16.430 --> 00:00:19.364
- Man: Get in.
- Get back!

6
00:00:23.602 --> 00:00:25.870
Guy's nuts.
Tried to steal my sister's purse.

7
00:00:25.904 --> 00:00:26.704
[ Panting ]

8
00:00:26.738 --> 00:00:28.073
You stole the purse. Jacob.

9
00:00:28.107 --> 00:00:30.541
Like the credit cards
and the Pontiac.

10
00:00:30.576 --> 00:00:32.043
How do you know my name?

11
00:00:32.078 --> 00:00:33.678
I'm surprised
you haven't stolen more.

12
00:00:33.712 --> 00:00:36.847
considering the situation
with your foster home.

13
00:00:36.881 --> 00:00:39.984
You know.
we've been watching you. Jacob.

14
00:00:40.018 --> 00:00:42.252
We may have
an opportunity for you.

15
00:00:42.287 --> 00:00:43.220
Who are you?

16
00:00:43.254 --> 00:00:44.321
W-what is this?

17
00:00:44.356 --> 00:00:46.056
According to our research.

18
00:00:46.091 --> 00:00:47.591
you have
some remarkable talents.

19
00:00:47.625 --> 00:00:48.925
You want the purse?
Take the purse.

20
00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:50.461
You ever stop to think
that the reason

21
00:00:50.495 --> 00:00:52.062
you have trouble relating
to other people

22
00:00:52.097 --> 00:00:54.263
is because you're special?

23
00:00:54.298 --> 00:00:58.101
That it's not you.
it's everyone else that's the problem?

24
00:00:58.135 --> 00:01:00.103
That's not what
social services says.

25
00:01:00.137 --> 00:01:02.005
Good old social services...

26
00:01:02.039 --> 00:01:05.308
Bureaucrats trained
in missing the point.

27
00:01:05.342 --> 00:01:08.777
We believe that
your delinquent inclinations

28
00:01:08.812 --> 00:01:12.584
are exactly what makes you
invaluable.

29
00:01:12.607 --> 00:01:15.456
It takes a certain kind
of courage.

30
00:01:15.490 --> 00:01:17.926
What are you talking about...
A job. a school?

31
00:01:17.960 --> 00:01:19.627
What is all this stuff?

32
00:01:19.662 --> 00:01:22.797
I told you. we have an opportunity.
if you're willing to take it...

33
00:01:22.831 --> 00:01:25.399
If you're smart enough
to take it.

34
00:01:25.434 --> 00:01:27.134
It's your choice. Jacob.

35
00:01:27.169 --> 00:01:28.334
You can get out

36
00:01:28.369 --> 00:01:29.803
and go back to the life
you've always known.

37
00:01:29.837 --> 00:01:31.071
or you can take a ride with me.

38
00:01:31.105 --> 00:01:33.807
and I can tell you
how to leave this life behind.

39
00:01:33.841 --> 00:01:37.277
I can help you become anything.

40
00:01:37.718 --> 00:01:40.473
Sync. corrected by icephoenix
www.addic7ed.com

41
00:01:43.091 --> 00:01:44.852
_

42
00:01:45.287 --> 00:01:47.453
Hey. Aram said
you were looking for me.

43
00:01:47.487 --> 00:01:48.754
Come in.
Close the door.

44
00:01:48.789 --> 00:01:49.989
What's going on?

45
00:01:50.023 --> 00:01:51.635
An assistant U.S. attorney
here in D.C.

46
00:01:51.659 --> 00:01:53.718
has impaneled a grand jury.

47
00:01:53.752 --> 00:01:56.221
He's looking into the death
of lieutenant Eugene Ames...

48
00:01:56.255 --> 00:01:57.355
A former harbormaster.

49
00:01:57.390 --> 00:01:59.690
I just got off the phone
with Detective Wilcox.

50
00:01:59.725 --> 00:02:01.825
We discussed the target
of his investigation.

51
00:02:01.859 --> 00:02:03.827
- You.
- Apparently. you encountered the victim

52
00:02:03.861 --> 00:02:04.895
the day he disappeared...

53
00:02:04.929 --> 00:02:07.033
Drew down on the man.
fed him some story

54
00:02:07.056 --> 00:02:09.317
about searching for fugitives
out of Cumberland Prison.

55
00:02:09.352 --> 00:02:11.319
There were no fugitives.

56
00:02:11.354 --> 00:02:12.588
No.

57
00:02:12.622 --> 00:02:15.156
When Wilcox confronted you.
you changed your story.

58
00:02:15.191 --> 00:02:17.826
Said you were there
on official business.

59
00:02:17.861 --> 00:02:19.861
They even had a witness.
but the guy recanted.

60
00:02:19.895 --> 00:02:22.430
Now Agent Cooper's
been subpoenaed

61
00:02:22.464 --> 00:02:24.365
to corroborate your story.

62
00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:27.201
They want to ask him under oath
if you're lying.

63
00:02:27.235 --> 00:02:29.804
We all know that
you weren't at that marina

64
00:02:29.838 --> 00:02:33.073
in your official capacity
as a member of this task force.

65
00:02:33.108 --> 00:02:36.315
So. you want to tell me
why the hell you were there?

66
00:02:37.670 --> 00:02:38.770
I can't.

67
00:02:38.804 --> 00:02:40.805
You're the target of
a federal murder investigation.

68
00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:43.308
You really think the best choice
at this point is to shut me out?

69
00:02:43.343 --> 00:02:45.377
You're right.
I didn't tell Wilcox the truth.

70
00:02:45.412 --> 00:02:47.979
But I am telling you the truth
when I say I didn't kill anyone.

71
00:02:48.014 --> 00:02:50.449
Look. Meera was dead.
You were in the hospital.

72
00:02:50.483 --> 00:02:54.085
I did what I thought
was necessary to stop Berlin.

73
00:02:54.119 --> 00:02:55.253
That's all I'm willing to say.

74
00:02:55.287 --> 00:02:57.221
You'll say far less than that.
Agent Keen.

75
00:02:57.256 --> 00:02:59.157
I've filed a motion
to quash the subpoena.

76
00:02:59.191 --> 00:03:01.725
Only 41 people know
this task force exists.

77
00:03:01.760 --> 00:03:04.728
I will not risk further exposure.
not by this.

78
00:03:04.763 --> 00:03:07.165
You'd better hope this motion works.
Agent Keen.

79
00:03:07.199 --> 00:03:09.899
'cause I'm telling you now.
if they put me under oath.

80
00:03:09.934 --> 00:03:11.901
I will not commit perjury
to protect you.

81
00:03:15.555 --> 00:03:17.387
_

82
00:03:18.109 --> 00:03:20.077
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Oh. sorry. man.

83
00:03:20.111 --> 00:03:21.878
Martin! Martin. Come on.

84
00:03:21.912 --> 00:03:24.187
I told you...
Denner sits at 9:00.

85
00:03:24.208 --> 00:03:26.176
I know. I know.
I got everything.

86
00:03:26.210 --> 00:03:27.276
Okay. look.

87
00:03:27.310 --> 00:03:29.379
I don't know what
we're walking into here.

88
00:03:29.413 --> 00:03:31.714
It's no small thing to indict
an active federal agent.

89
00:03:31.749 --> 00:03:33.750
I'm on to something.
She's guilty.

90
00:03:33.784 --> 00:03:36.051
Denner is the perfect guy
to hear this. okay?

91
00:03:36.086 --> 00:03:38.020
He's former
criminal defense attorney.

92
00:03:38.054 --> 00:03:40.055
- former Berkeley law professor.
- Huh.

93
00:03:40.090 --> 00:03:42.792
And he's a staunch proponent
of government transparency.

94
00:03:42.826 --> 00:03:43.992
Well. that's promising.

95
00:03:44.026 --> 00:03:45.660
We're going to five?

96
00:03:45.695 --> 00:03:48.497
Yeah.
They switched the courtroom.

97
00:03:48.531 --> 00:03:50.866
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Mr. Markin. Detective.

98
00:03:50.900 --> 00:03:52.801
Step over to the checkpoint.
please.

99
00:03:52.835 --> 00:03:54.403
Where the hell is everybody?

100
00:03:54.437 --> 00:03:57.038
What... What is this?

101
00:03:57.072 --> 00:03:58.940
I'll need you to surrender
your mobile devices.

102
00:03:58.974 --> 00:04:00.574
anything that you have
that can be used

103
00:04:00.609 --> 00:04:01.975
to record
today's proceedings...

104
00:04:02.010 --> 00:04:04.211
Laptops. pens. tablets.

105
00:04:04.245 --> 00:04:07.415
You... You want my pens?

106
00:04:07.449 --> 00:04:08.348
This is crazy.

107
00:04:08.383 --> 00:04:09.850
This will only take a moment.

108
00:04:09.885 --> 00:04:12.520
Judge Denner: I'm afraid I've
been doing this for a while.

109
00:04:12.554 --> 00:04:14.087
but this is certainly a first.

110
00:04:14.122 --> 00:04:16.791
Not only did you switch my courtroom.
you closed it.

111
00:04:16.825 --> 00:04:18.858
And then you closed
the entire floor.

112
00:04:18.893 --> 00:04:20.059
My apologies. Your Honor.

113
00:04:20.093 --> 00:04:21.828
but I trust
the measures we've taken

114
00:04:21.862 --> 00:04:24.196
will indicate how seriously
we take this proceeding

115
00:04:24.231 --> 00:04:26.399
and the threat it poses
to our national security.

116
00:04:26.434 --> 00:04:27.366
So indicated.

117
00:04:27.401 --> 00:04:28.468
That said. I fail to understand

118
00:04:28.502 --> 00:04:30.837
how a routine
grand jury investigation

119
00:04:30.871 --> 00:04:32.305
into a local homicide

120
00:04:32.339 --> 00:04:35.541
justifies a dog-and-pony show
of such dramatic proportions.

121
00:04:35.575 --> 00:04:38.710
Wright: There's nothing routine
about this matter. Your Honor.

122
00:04:38.745 --> 00:04:40.078
On behalf
of the justice department.

123
00:04:40.112 --> 00:04:41.814
I'm here to ask the court
to quash the subpoena

124
00:04:41.848 --> 00:04:43.582
issued to
Assistant Director Cooper

125
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:44.817
without delay.

126
00:04:44.851 --> 00:04:47.453
For national security reasons. yes...
Such as?

127
00:04:49.989 --> 00:04:52.723
Oh. come on. Ms. Wright.
Don't I even get a ballpark?

128
00:04:52.758 --> 00:04:56.160
"To insulate covert
intelligence capacities"?

129
00:04:56.194 --> 00:04:59.296
"To protect an informant
in an active operational zone"?

130
00:04:59.331 --> 00:05:02.500
With respect.
I don't appreciate your sarcasm. Your Honor.

131
00:05:02.534 --> 00:05:03.701
Really?

132
00:05:03.735 --> 00:05:05.736
Well. here's what I don't appreciate.
counsel.

133
00:05:05.771 --> 00:05:07.705
I don't appreciate
being instructed

134
00:05:07.739 --> 00:05:10.831
as to what will or will not
happen in my courtroom.

135
00:05:10.854 --> 00:05:13.390
Your Honor. if I may...

136
00:05:13.414 --> 00:05:16.467
A citizen of this district
has been brutally murdered...

137
00:05:16.501 --> 00:05:18.635
Not just a citizen.
but a public servant.

138
00:05:18.659 --> 00:05:20.556
a lieutenant
for the Metro P.D.

139
00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:22.891
And the people
have a right to access

140
00:05:22.925 --> 00:05:24.192
and evaluate all evidence...

141
00:05:24.227 --> 00:05:25.426
No. they don't.

142
00:05:25.461 --> 00:05:27.094
We have a fundamental right
to seek justice...

143
00:05:27.128 --> 00:05:28.696
Look.
we are here as a courtesy.

144
00:05:28.731 --> 00:05:31.265
...and we shouldn't have
to take the government's word

145
00:05:31.299 --> 00:05:33.835
for the fact that national
security might be involved.

146
00:05:33.869 --> 00:05:34.935
It's our call to make.

147
00:05:34.970 --> 00:05:36.537
We're not asking
for a second opinion.

148
00:05:36.572 --> 00:05:38.005
You're protecting
a federal agent.

149
00:05:38.039 --> 00:05:39.440
Mr. Markin.
control your witness.

150
00:05:39.475 --> 00:05:40.808
I have a good-faith basis

151
00:05:40.843 --> 00:05:42.076
to believe that Agent Keen
is involved...

152
00:05:42.110 --> 00:05:43.209
Markin: Marty.
[ Gavel bangs ]

153
00:05:43.244 --> 00:05:44.611
- It's a cover-up.
- Enough.

154
00:05:47.996 --> 00:05:50.116
Okay. Ms. Wright.
I take your point.

155
00:05:50.150 --> 00:05:51.618
Somebody has to make the call

156
00:05:51.652 --> 00:05:54.020
as to what does or does not
rise to the level

157
00:05:54.054 --> 00:05:55.622
of a national security concern.

158
00:05:55.656 --> 00:05:56.790
And we agree.

159
00:05:56.824 --> 00:05:59.259
That call should not be made
by the people

160
00:05:59.293 --> 00:06:01.927
or Detective Wilcox
or even a grand jury.

161
00:06:01.961 --> 00:06:02.961
Thank you. Your Honor.

162
00:06:02.996 --> 00:06:04.196
It's <i>my</i> job.

163
00:06:04.230 --> 00:06:06.799
I will hear the
Justice Department's argument

164
00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:08.534
- in chambers.
- Objection!

165
00:06:08.568 --> 00:06:12.669
And if I agree that
national security is endangered.

166
00:06:12.692 --> 00:06:14.360
I will quash the subpoena.

167
00:06:14.383 --> 00:06:15.941
and the investigation
along with it.

168
00:06:15.975 --> 00:06:17.442
You have no authority.

169
00:06:19.512 --> 00:06:22.580
Haven't we had enough
government suppression. counsel?

170
00:06:22.615 --> 00:06:24.449
Haven't we seen what happens

171
00:06:24.483 --> 00:06:27.151
when government's actions
go unchecked?

172
00:06:27.185 --> 00:06:28.862
Now. you decide.

173
00:06:28.886 --> 00:06:30.522
I can hold you and your agents
in contempt

174
00:06:30.556 --> 00:06:32.791
and have my officers
take you into custody.

175
00:06:32.825 --> 00:06:34.958
or you can comply
with my ruling.

176
00:06:34.992 --> 00:06:36.760
Choose. Right now.

177
00:06:37.845 --> 00:06:39.763
You've made a mistake. Richard.

178
00:06:41.766 --> 00:06:42.866
I agree. Reven.

179
00:06:42.901 --> 00:06:45.891
I should've been
a dermatologist.

180
00:06:45.914 --> 00:06:48.639
I will see Agent Keen
in chambers in five minutes.

181
00:06:48.673 --> 00:06:50.340
We're adjourned.
[ Gavel bangs ]

182
00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:58.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

183
00:07:06.256 --> 00:07:07.456
Liz: Thank you.

184
00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:08.857
[ Door opens ]

185
00:07:08.891 --> 00:07:12.861
Agent Keen.
you have the right to an attorney.

186
00:07:12.895 --> 00:07:14.796
but if you do request counsel

187
00:07:14.831 --> 00:07:16.932
or refuse to answer
my questions.

188
00:07:16.966 --> 00:07:20.110
this hearing is over.
and I will determine

189
00:07:20.134 --> 00:07:22.969
if your case should proceed
in open court

190
00:07:23.003 --> 00:07:26.072
based on the facts
already in evidence.

191
00:07:26.106 --> 00:07:27.940
Are we clear to proceed?

192
00:07:28.874 --> 00:07:30.154
Yes. Your Honor.

193
00:07:30.178 --> 00:07:33.064
Raise your right hand
and repeat after me.

194
00:07:33.099 --> 00:07:34.400
I. Elizabeth Keen...

195
00:07:34.434 --> 00:07:36.334
I understand we have a problem.

196
00:07:36.369 --> 00:07:38.370
Agent Keen's testifying
in camera

197
00:07:38.405 --> 00:07:41.947
about the investigation as we speak...
Judge's chambers.

198
00:07:41.961 --> 00:07:43.512
Eugene Ames was a cop.

199
00:07:43.536 --> 00:07:45.563
The judge will want
his murder avenged.

200
00:07:45.598 --> 00:07:47.786
Best case.
she'll be charged as an accessory.

201
00:07:47.810 --> 00:07:49.802
And this task force
will be shut down.

202
00:07:51.414 --> 00:07:52.671
The Major.

203
00:07:52.705 --> 00:07:54.406
Major? What major?

204
00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:56.141
Not a <i>what</i>. Donald. a <i>who</i>...

205
00:07:56.176 --> 00:07:58.010
the next name on the Blacklist.

206
00:07:58.044 --> 00:07:59.351
Have you not been
paying attention

207
00:07:59.372 --> 00:08:00.606
to a word we've been saying?

208
00:08:00.640 --> 00:08:01.907
Agent Keen will be charged...

209
00:08:01.941 --> 00:08:05.143
The Major runs
a finishing school of sorts...

210
00:08:05.177 --> 00:08:07.513
The most reputable of its kind.

211
00:08:07.547 --> 00:08:12.551
He recruits wayward children.
orphans. delinquents. outcasts.

212
00:08:12.585 --> 00:08:16.120
but only boys and girls
of superior intelligence

213
00:08:16.154 --> 00:08:19.757
who exhibit very specific
sociopathic tendencies.

214
00:08:19.791 --> 00:08:23.293
He then cultivates them into charming.
well-educated.

215
00:08:23.328 --> 00:08:26.130
cultured.
attractive adults who are capable

216
00:08:26.164 --> 00:08:28.432
of dangerous
and horrible things.

217
00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:30.267
All that matters is Agent Keen.

218
00:08:30.301 --> 00:08:34.203
Which is why
we must find the Major.

219
00:08:34.238 --> 00:08:36.873
He and I had a rather
significant falling out.

220
00:08:36.908 --> 00:08:38.241
and I can't locate him.

221
00:08:38.275 --> 00:08:40.710
which is why you need
to put me in a room

222
00:08:40.745 --> 00:08:43.379
with the Malaysian
Deputy Minister to the U.N.

223
00:08:43.414 --> 00:08:45.982
You want the FBI
to invite a U.N. diplomat

224
00:08:46.017 --> 00:08:48.051
- to meet with you?
- Of course not.

225
00:08:48.085 --> 00:08:49.485
Inviting him for a chat

226
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:52.888
with one of your most wanted
criminals would be ludicrous.

227
00:08:52.923 --> 00:08:54.456
You'll need to abduct him.

228
00:08:54.490 --> 00:08:56.625
Okay. hold on.
That's not gonna happen.

229
00:08:56.660 --> 00:08:58.060
Why on earth would...

230
00:08:58.094 --> 00:09:00.563
Because he has secrets
I can exploit.

231
00:09:00.597 --> 00:09:03.732
Listen. I'd snatch him myself.
but time is short.

232
00:09:03.767 --> 00:09:05.601
so. I'm sorry.
you're going to have to do it for me.

233
00:09:05.635 --> 00:09:07.435
You're asking us
to commit a felony.

234
00:09:07.469 --> 00:09:09.070
Call it what you will. Harold.

235
00:09:09.104 --> 00:09:10.772
But if you want
to prevent Agent Keen

236
00:09:10.806 --> 00:09:12.073
from going to prison.

237
00:09:12.107 --> 00:09:15.944
you need to abduct
Deputy Minister Mamat Krishnan.

238
00:09:30.333 --> 00:09:31.872
Minister Krishnan!

239
00:09:31.892 --> 00:09:34.661
Minister Krishnan!

240
00:09:34.695 --> 00:09:37.030
Aah! Aah!

241
00:09:37.064 --> 00:09:38.999
Aah! Aah!

242
00:09:39.033 --> 00:09:41.067
[ Vehicle door slams ]

243
00:09:41.102 --> 00:09:43.603
[ Tires squeal ]

244
00:09:43.638 --> 00:09:45.630
Can you please state
your full name and occupation

245
00:09:45.643 --> 00:09:46.609
for the record?

246
00:09:46.644 --> 00:09:47.710
Elizabeth Scott Keen.

247
00:09:47.745 --> 00:09:49.245
I'm a special agent
for the FBI.

248
00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:50.512
And your assignment?

249
00:09:50.546 --> 00:09:52.180
My assignment is classified.

250
00:09:52.214 --> 00:09:53.181
Classified how?

251
00:09:53.215 --> 00:09:54.949
I'm part
of a black-book task force

252
00:09:54.984 --> 00:09:56.184
that investigates cases

253
00:09:56.218 --> 00:09:57.886
brought forward
by a criminal informant.

254
00:09:57.920 --> 00:09:59.187
What informant?

255
00:09:59.221 --> 00:10:01.990
Your Honor. with all respect.
I can't divulge the name...

256
00:10:02.024 --> 00:10:03.659
Agent Keen.
I'm here to determine

257
00:10:03.693 --> 00:10:06.261
whether the work you do
should remain secret.

258
00:10:06.296 --> 00:10:09.163
The burden is on you
to convince me that it should.

259
00:10:09.197 --> 00:10:10.498
If you choose to not even try.

260
00:10:10.532 --> 00:10:12.500
we will be having
this conversation in open court.

261
00:10:12.534 --> 00:10:14.201
- so I need to know...
- Raymond Reddington.

262
00:10:17.014 --> 00:10:19.774
Your source is
Raymond Reddington?

263
00:10:19.808 --> 00:10:21.175
Yes.

264
00:10:21.209 --> 00:10:24.944
I thought Reddington recently
escaped from a black site

265
00:10:24.978 --> 00:10:26.245
and his whereabouts
are unknown.

266
00:10:26.280 --> 00:10:27.893
It was a cover.

267
00:10:27.916 --> 00:10:29.454
He was never captured?

268
00:10:29.478 --> 00:10:31.685
He was captured.
We helped him escape.

269
00:10:31.709 --> 00:10:35.054
Are you telling me a fugitive
on the FBI's most-wanted list

270
00:10:35.088 --> 00:10:37.557
is actually an informant
for the FBI?

271
00:10:37.591 --> 00:10:40.126
Which is why what we do
must remain a secret.

272
00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:42.828
If criminals knew Reddington
was working with the FBI.

273
00:10:42.862 --> 00:10:43.995
then he would be of no value.

274
00:10:44.030 --> 00:10:45.130
How old are you. Agent Keen?

275
00:10:45.164 --> 00:10:46.298
30.

276
00:10:46.333 --> 00:10:48.835
And how long have you been
with the Bureau?

277
00:10:51.723 --> 00:10:54.473
I... I've been a profiler
for 18 months.

278
00:10:55.407 --> 00:10:58.210
So. tell me.
if the work of this task force

279
00:10:58.244 --> 00:11:01.546
really does affect
national security.

280
00:11:02.336 --> 00:11:04.074
why would the FBI pick someone

281
00:11:04.091 --> 00:11:06.358
with as little experience
as you to be on it?

282
00:11:06.393 --> 00:11:07.859
The FBI didn't pick me.

283
00:11:07.894 --> 00:11:09.695
and I didn't want to have
anything to do with it.

284
00:11:09.729 --> 00:11:11.730
You didn't want any part of it.
the FBI didn't pick you.

285
00:11:11.764 --> 00:11:14.100
So how did you
come to be on it?

286
00:11:14.134 --> 00:11:15.500
Reddington chose me.

287
00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:18.069
Why would he choose you?
Why you?

288
00:11:18.104 --> 00:11:20.037
I thought we were here
to talk about Eugene Ames.

289
00:11:20.072 --> 00:11:23.541
What. he just knocked
on your door one day?

290
00:11:24.929 --> 00:11:26.777
No.
He sent a helicopter.

291
00:11:26.812 --> 00:11:29.714
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

292
00:11:29.748 --> 00:11:31.882
[ Sirens wail ]

293
00:11:31.917 --> 00:11:36.520
I had a very simple life...
A husband I loved. a dog.

294
00:11:36.554 --> 00:11:39.523
It was my first day on the job.

295
00:11:39.557 --> 00:11:43.393
And suddenly.
I was flying over restricted airspace.

296
00:11:43.428 --> 00:11:45.962
They sat me down with
Deputy Director Harold Cooper.

297
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:48.432
Do you find it odd
Reddington surrendered himself

298
00:11:48.466 --> 00:11:50.566
the day you started
working as a profiler?

299
00:11:50.601 --> 00:11:51.867
I'm sorry.
what does this have to do

300
00:11:51.901 --> 00:11:53.269
with what happened
with Mr. Ames?

301
00:11:53.303 --> 00:11:56.005
Well. as I understand it.
the death of the harbormaster

302
00:11:56.039 --> 00:11:58.641
came in connection with
your work on this task force.

303
00:11:58.675 --> 00:11:59.842
That is true.

304
00:11:59.876 --> 00:12:00.976
but you don't need all
these details to determine...

305
00:12:01.011 --> 00:12:02.478
Tell me about
the first meeting.

306
00:12:02.513 --> 00:12:03.812
With Ames?

307
00:12:03.847 --> 00:12:05.581
With Reddington.

308
00:12:07.450 --> 00:12:11.286
[ Machinery whirs ]

309
00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:14.122
I'd never been so terrified.

310
00:12:14.157 --> 00:12:17.459
We'd studied him at Quantico...
His crimes. his profile.

311
00:12:17.493 --> 00:12:20.728
But when we sat down.
he spoke as if he knew me.

312
00:12:20.763 --> 00:12:22.730
Agent Keen. what a pleasure.

313
00:12:22.765 --> 00:12:23.564
But you said
you didn't know him.

314
00:12:23.598 --> 00:12:24.798
you'd never met him.

315
00:12:24.832 --> 00:12:27.168
Did he. what.
just expect you to believe him?

316
00:12:27.202 --> 00:12:29.303
[ Laughing ]
No. of course not.

317
00:12:29.337 --> 00:12:31.738
I had no idea what he expected.

318
00:12:31.773 --> 00:12:35.075
I'm a criminal.
Criminals are notorious liars.

319
00:12:35.109 --> 00:12:36.710
Everything about me is a lie.

320
00:12:36.744 --> 00:12:39.180
You must have known
how strange all of this was.

321
00:12:39.214 --> 00:12:40.313
Of course I did.

322
00:12:40.347 --> 00:12:42.975
And yet you agreed
to work with him.

323
00:12:44.385 --> 00:12:45.652
Well. he had intel.

324
00:12:45.686 --> 00:12:48.020
He said a girl was going to be taken.
a general's daughter.

325
00:12:48.055 --> 00:12:49.088
We had to act.

326
00:12:49.122 --> 00:12:50.122
And since he would
only talk to me...

327
00:12:50.157 --> 00:12:50.956
Only you?

328
00:12:50.991 --> 00:12:52.525
He insists upon it.

329
00:12:52.560 --> 00:12:54.360
A woman he'd never met.

330
00:12:55.266 --> 00:12:57.029
Like I said.
no one believed me.

331
00:12:57.064 --> 00:12:58.963
And this intel
about the girl...

332
00:12:58.998 --> 00:13:01.367
Was it accurate?
Was she taken?

333
00:13:03.670 --> 00:13:05.804
[ Tires screech ]

334
00:13:05.838 --> 00:13:07.639
[ Screams ]

335
00:13:07.674 --> 00:13:08.907
Yes.

336
00:13:08.941 --> 00:13:10.275
[ Screams ]

337
00:13:10.310 --> 00:13:11.677
These men are gonna come.
and they're gonna take you.

338
00:13:11.711 --> 00:13:12.877
Are they gonna hurt me?

339
00:13:12.912 --> 00:13:14.645
They're not gonna
hurt you. honey.

340
00:13:14.680 --> 00:13:15.680
I'm gonna find you.

341
00:13:20.732 --> 00:13:23.787
With Reddington's help.
we were able to save her

342
00:13:23.822 --> 00:13:25.956
and prevent
an attack on D.C.

343
00:13:25.990 --> 00:13:27.157
But the cost...

344
00:13:28.966 --> 00:13:30.294
...was...

345
00:13:30.329 --> 00:13:32.729
Tom.

346
00:13:32.763 --> 00:13:35.551
All I wanted was my life back.

347
00:13:35.575 --> 00:13:38.393
but Reddington had other plans.

348
00:13:38.417 --> 00:13:40.370
He told the deputy director

349
00:13:40.404 --> 00:13:43.240
that he had a list of criminals
he could help us find.

350
00:13:43.274 --> 00:13:44.674
and that was only the first.

351
00:13:44.709 --> 00:13:47.210
- Judge Denner: The first what?
- Name... On the list.

352
00:13:47.245 --> 00:13:48.910
He told us.
if we cut him a deal.

353
00:13:48.945 --> 00:13:51.347
that he could help us capture
the kinds of criminals

354
00:13:51.381 --> 00:13:53.815
the FBI can't find because
we don't know they exist.

355
00:13:53.850 --> 00:13:54.883
[ Sighs ]
One day.

356
00:13:54.917 --> 00:13:56.818
you and I will be talking
about this moment

357
00:13:56.853 --> 00:13:58.186
in front of a Senate hearing.

358
00:13:58.221 --> 00:13:59.855
Were you ordered
to work with Reddington?

359
00:13:59.889 --> 00:14:00.856
No.

360
00:14:00.890 --> 00:14:03.559
And he couldn't force you.

361
00:14:03.593 --> 00:14:07.762
So I'm curious...
If he knew nothing about you.

362
00:14:08.534 --> 00:14:12.700
if his implications of some
shared connection were false.

363
00:14:13.256 --> 00:14:14.669
why did you continue?

364
00:14:14.703 --> 00:14:18.371
Because it turns out.
they weren't.

365
00:14:20.242 --> 00:14:23.076
They weren't false.

366
00:14:23.110 --> 00:14:27.381
He knew things about me...
Things I didn't even know...

367
00:14:28.309 --> 00:14:30.463
About my husband at the time.

368
00:14:30.487 --> 00:14:32.486
Whatever connection
he thought we had.

369
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:35.155
whatever history
he was implying we shared.

370
00:14:35.189 --> 00:14:36.189
I didn't care.

371
00:14:36.223 --> 00:14:38.592
You've discovered
something curious

372
00:14:38.626 --> 00:14:41.694
about your husband.
haven't you. Lizzy?

373
00:14:41.728 --> 00:14:44.139
He wanted me for a reason...

374
00:14:45.501 --> 00:14:47.566
And I wanted to know why.

375
00:14:51.905 --> 00:14:53.639
That man has
diplomatic immunity.

376
00:14:53.674 --> 00:14:55.441
- If anyone finds out...
- They won't.

377
00:14:55.475 --> 00:14:56.641
How can you be so sure?

378
00:14:56.676 --> 00:14:58.075
You need to leave. Donald.

379
00:14:58.110 --> 00:14:59.711
You'd better have
a damned good reason for...

380
00:14:59.745 --> 00:15:01.245
You need to leave.

381
00:15:20.131 --> 00:15:21.632
[ Door closes ]

382
00:15:26.471 --> 00:15:28.605
Let's have a little chat.

383
00:15:33.006 --> 00:15:35.190
_

384
00:15:35.214 --> 00:15:38.316
[ German metal music playing ]

385
00:15:50.165 --> 00:15:52.067
[ Conversing in German ]

386
00:15:52.091 --> 00:15:54.181
_

387
00:15:54.204 --> 00:15:56.365
_

388
00:15:56.388 --> 00:15:57.656
_

389
00:15:57.679 --> 00:15:58.536
_

390
00:15:58.560 --> 00:15:59.605
_

391
00:15:59.622 --> 00:16:02.369
_

392
00:16:02.392 --> 00:16:04.823
_

393
00:16:04.840 --> 00:16:07.188
_

394
00:16:12.527 --> 00:16:15.475
_

395
00:16:15.486 --> 00:16:18.363
_

396
00:16:19.425 --> 00:16:20.916
_

397
00:16:30.022 --> 00:16:31.428
_

398
00:16:35.004 --> 00:16:36.371
[ Laughter ]

399
00:16:48.535 --> 00:16:50.364
I don't know what you want.

400
00:16:51.576 --> 00:16:53.200
but you won't
get away with this.

401
00:16:53.234 --> 00:16:56.837
I've always been leery
of the United Nations.

402
00:16:57.374 --> 00:17:02.174
The very concept is
comically dichotomous...

403
00:17:02.209 --> 00:17:05.778
Nations putting
their self-interests aside

404
00:17:05.813 --> 00:17:08.976
in the hopes of building
a global community.

405
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:11.340
holding hands and Kumbaya?

406
00:17:11.374 --> 00:17:14.307
[ Laughing ]
I mean. honestly. it's like kindergarten.

407
00:17:14.321 --> 00:17:15.548
Do you have rug time?

408
00:17:15.567 --> 00:17:17.434
I did love rug time.

409
00:17:17.468 --> 00:17:18.702
Who are you?

410
00:17:18.737 --> 00:17:20.971
It doesn't matter who <i>I</i> am.

411
00:17:21.471 --> 00:17:23.440
What matters is who <i>you</i> are...

412
00:17:23.474 --> 00:17:26.543
A secret agent
trained by the Major.

413
00:17:26.577 --> 00:17:30.114
working away as
a dedicated public servant.

414
00:17:30.148 --> 00:17:32.415
when. in fact. you're an asset

415
00:17:32.450 --> 00:17:35.484
inserted into your country's
diplomatic corps

416
00:17:35.518 --> 00:17:36.986
by the Sinaloa Cartel

417
00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:39.055
to help them get
a foothold in Asia.

418
00:17:39.089 --> 00:17:40.123
What do you want?

419
00:17:40.157 --> 00:17:44.160
The man who created you...
The Major.

420
00:17:44.194 --> 00:17:46.095
Tell me his location.

421
00:17:46.130 --> 00:17:50.232
or I'll tip the cartel
you've been outed.

422
00:17:50.266 --> 00:17:53.101
Tell me.
does Hernandez remove the tongues

423
00:17:53.136 --> 00:17:56.332
before the executions or after?

424
00:17:56.355 --> 00:17:57.239
Please...

425
00:17:57.273 --> 00:17:59.440
I'm not interested
in your business.

426
00:17:59.464 --> 00:18:01.977
I'm not here to expose you.

427
00:18:02.011 --> 00:18:04.412
I'm only interested
in the Major.

428
00:18:04.446 --> 00:18:06.781
Where is he?

429
00:18:06.815 --> 00:18:10.172
Let's talk about Tom Keen.

430
00:18:11.346 --> 00:18:14.444
You said that Reddington
knew things about him.

431
00:18:14.468 --> 00:18:16.698
What kind of things?

432
00:18:16.722 --> 00:18:21.023
Tom Keen... The man I married.
he was a fiction.

433
00:18:21.046 --> 00:18:22.667
He didn't exist.

434
00:18:22.690 --> 00:18:23.730
But Detective Wilcox says

435
00:18:23.765 --> 00:18:26.266
that you and this fiction
killed Eugene Ames.

436
00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:27.566
That's impossible.

437
00:18:27.601 --> 00:18:28.701
And why is that?

438
00:18:28.735 --> 00:18:29.735
Because Tom Keen died

439
00:18:29.770 --> 00:18:31.337
four months before
Mr. Ames was killed.

440
00:18:31.371 --> 00:18:33.206
Wilcox is under the impression

441
00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:35.374
that your husband
is very much alive.

442
00:18:35.409 --> 00:18:36.810
Did you report his death?

443
00:18:36.844 --> 00:18:37.643
No.

444
00:18:37.678 --> 00:18:39.012
Why not?

445
00:18:39.046 --> 00:18:40.513
Because I killed him.

446
00:18:40.547 --> 00:18:42.247
You killed your husband?

447
00:18:42.282 --> 00:18:45.284
My ex-husband. Yes.
I shot him in self defense.

448
00:18:51.713 --> 00:18:54.426
"He didn't exist."
What does that mean?

449
00:18:56.116 --> 00:19:00.497
The man that I married...
He was perfect.

450
00:19:00.532 --> 00:19:02.266
Tom:
When I'm with you. Liz.

451
00:19:02.301 --> 00:19:04.836
I feel like
I don't need to pretend.

452
00:19:04.870 --> 00:19:06.838
I know that you accept me

453
00:19:06.872 --> 00:19:08.405
for who I really am.

454
00:19:08.440 --> 00:19:09.773
and that is a gift

455
00:19:09.808 --> 00:19:12.109
that I thank God for every day.

456
00:19:12.144 --> 00:19:14.845
He kind. smart. a teacher.

457
00:19:14.879 --> 00:19:17.480
Ha! Ha!
[ Cheering. laughter. applause ]

458
00:19:21.452 --> 00:19:22.853
Or so I thought.

459
00:19:22.887 --> 00:19:24.754
They say love is blind.

460
00:19:24.788 --> 00:19:26.022
I certainly was.

461
00:19:26.057 --> 00:19:27.357
Blind to what?

462
00:19:27.391 --> 00:19:29.826
To the fact that our entire
relationship was a lie.

463
00:19:29.861 --> 00:19:32.161
that my husband was a spy.

464
00:19:32.184 --> 00:19:33.262
The only reason he was with me

465
00:19:33.296 --> 00:19:35.865
was because of my connection
to Reddington.

466
00:19:35.899 --> 00:19:37.900
The connection you say
didn't exist.

467
00:19:37.934 --> 00:19:40.302
I didn't know about it.
but others did.

468
00:19:40.337 --> 00:19:43.105
And you learned your husband
was a spy from Reddington?

469
00:19:43.139 --> 00:19:46.742
Sort of.
I had to find out for myself.

470
00:19:46.776 --> 00:19:48.877
And when you did find out.
what did you do then?

471
00:19:48.911 --> 00:19:51.479
I spied on him.

472
00:19:51.513 --> 00:19:53.214
Interrogated
the people in his life.

473
00:19:53.249 --> 00:19:54.916
tried to find out
who he worked for.

474
00:19:54.950 --> 00:19:56.150
And did you find out?

475
00:19:56.218 --> 00:20:00.188
Not before he realized
that I knew.

476
00:20:01.623 --> 00:20:03.958
How did that conversation go?

477
00:20:13.693 --> 00:20:14.938
It was heated.

478
00:20:14.961 --> 00:20:16.270
Is that when you murdered him?

479
00:20:16.304 --> 00:20:18.872
[ Gunshots ]

480
00:20:19.807 --> 00:20:21.474
I didn't murder him.

481
00:20:21.509 --> 00:20:25.399
His boss. Berlin.
he ordered Tom to abduct me...

482
00:20:25.422 --> 00:20:27.146
Use me as leverage
to get to Reddington.

483
00:20:27.180 --> 00:20:28.647
I had a gun to my head.

484
00:20:28.681 --> 00:20:30.016
That's why I shot him.

485
00:20:30.050 --> 00:20:31.817
- That's convenient.
- What is?

486
00:20:31.851 --> 00:20:34.987
Using your job to justify
shooting your lying husband.

487
00:20:35.022 --> 00:20:36.555
Did Reddington want you
to shoot him?

488
00:20:36.589 --> 00:20:38.090
What difference does it make?

489
00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:39.958
I'm simply pointing out
that shooting your husband

490
00:20:39.992 --> 00:20:41.859
must have been a relief
to both you and Reddington.

491
00:20:41.894 --> 00:20:43.494
No.
you're calling me a murderer.

492
00:20:43.529 --> 00:20:44.595
I'm simply gathering the facts.

493
00:20:44.630 --> 00:20:45.931
You're implying
that my allegiance

494
00:20:45.965 --> 00:20:47.232
is as much with Reddington
than with the task force.

495
00:20:47.266 --> 00:20:48.800
Agent Keen.
what exactly is your relationship. then.

496
00:20:48.834 --> 00:20:50.201
with Raymond Reddington?

497
00:20:50.236 --> 00:20:51.436
He's my C.I..

498
00:20:51.470 --> 00:20:53.071
and if you want
to air that out in open court.

499
00:20:53.105 --> 00:20:56.141
go right ahead.
but do not question where my loyalties lie!

500
00:21:02.346 --> 00:21:04.681
Tell me about this task force...
How it works.

501
00:21:04.715 --> 00:21:06.917
[ Sighs ]
I told you. He has a list.

502
00:21:06.952 --> 00:21:08.485
Of criminals
you don't know exist.

503
00:21:08.519 --> 00:21:09.920
That sounds like
an empty promise.

504
00:21:09.955 --> 00:21:10.921
You'd be surprised.

505
00:21:10.956 --> 00:21:12.489
Humor me.

506
00:21:13.876 --> 00:21:16.592
There was a man
named Milton Bobbit

507
00:21:16.626 --> 00:21:18.094
who devised an ingenious way

508
00:21:18.128 --> 00:21:21.564
to turn terminally ill
patients into assassins.

509
00:21:21.598 --> 00:21:24.867
all while working as an
unassuming insurance adjuster.

510
00:21:24.935 --> 00:21:28.704
The Courier moves high-value
commodities under his skin.

511
00:21:28.738 --> 00:21:32.441
The Alchemist makes people
disappear by changing their DNA.

512
00:21:32.475 --> 00:21:34.609
None of this is possible.

513
00:21:34.643 --> 00:21:36.011
That's what we thought.

514
00:21:39.415 --> 00:21:42.384
How many of these cases
has Reddington given to you?

515
00:21:42.418 --> 00:21:43.385
Man: Yeah!

516
00:21:43.419 --> 00:21:45.753
[ Machine buzzes ]

517
00:21:48.457 --> 00:21:49.590
[ Tires screech ]

518
00:21:51.726 --> 00:21:53.560
[ Gunfire ]

519
00:21:53.595 --> 00:21:55.562
[ Explosion ]

520
00:21:55.597 --> 00:21:59.633
♪ Like a man on the run

521
00:21:59.667 --> 00:22:02.936
♪ I ain't got no place to hide

522
00:22:02.971 --> 00:22:06.139
♪ got one hand on my weapon

523
00:22:06.173 --> 00:22:10.310
♪ pray that God is on my side

524
00:22:10.344 --> 00:22:12.812
♪ your skin looks so cold

525
00:22:12.846 --> 00:22:16.383
♪ your eyes. they rob me blind

526
00:22:16.417 --> 00:22:19.886
♪ but your spell
takes its hold on me ♪

527
00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.888
♪ I got mischief on my mind

528
00:22:22.922 --> 00:22:27.192
♪ yeah. hocus pocus

529
00:22:27.227 --> 00:22:30.562
♪ first she's there.
and now she's gone ♪

530
00:22:30.596 --> 00:22:32.231
♪ it's the heist

531
00:22:33.933 --> 00:22:37.136
♪ try your luck
on the roll of the dice ♪

532
00:22:37.170 --> 00:22:39.904
♪ it's the heist

533
00:22:39.938 --> 00:22:43.607
♪ better watch your back.
might take your life ♪

534
00:22:43.642 --> 00:22:45.609
♪ it's the heist

535
00:22:45.644 --> 00:22:47.945
He keeps us busy.

536
00:22:49.894 --> 00:22:51.303
_

537
00:23:19.310 --> 00:23:21.277
[ Over stereo ]
♪ <i>dancin' in the moonlight</i> ♪

538
00:23:21.312 --> 00:23:23.279
♪ <i>everybody's feelin'</i>
<i>warm and bright</i> ♪

539
00:23:23.314 --> 00:23:24.214
[ Tires screech ]

540
00:23:24.248 --> 00:23:25.248
[ Vehicle departs ]

541
00:23:28.842 --> 00:23:30.099
I got nothing to say to you.

542
00:23:30.122 --> 00:23:31.971
You know Agent Keen
is in court today?

543
00:23:32.005 --> 00:23:33.906
She's telling the whole story.

544
00:23:33.940 --> 00:23:36.242
Well. her <i>version</i> of the story.
anyway.

545
00:23:36.276 --> 00:23:38.010
She says she never saw you
on the boat

546
00:23:38.044 --> 00:23:40.045
and that if the harbormaster
turned up dead.

547
00:23:40.080 --> 00:23:41.927
it's because you must
have killed him.

548
00:23:41.951 --> 00:23:42.905
You're lying.

549
00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:45.541
No. <i>she's</i> lying.

550
00:23:45.575 --> 00:23:48.177
We both know it.

551
00:23:48.211 --> 00:23:50.045
But you're the one
who's gonna pay the price.

552
00:23:50.079 --> 00:23:52.214
Look. this is the last chance
I'm gonna give you.

553
00:23:52.249 --> 00:23:53.582
I told you my story already.

554
00:23:53.617 --> 00:23:55.384
Then you recanted.

555
00:23:55.418 --> 00:23:57.085
You could get the death penalty.
Sam.

556
00:23:57.120 --> 00:23:59.054
Man.
I already took a bullet for my troubles.

557
00:23:59.088 --> 00:24:01.922
Ain't no way that I'm gonna get
the death penalty. too.

558
00:24:01.957 --> 00:24:03.191
Nice try.
but you don't have the evidence.

559
00:24:03.225 --> 00:24:06.927
Hold on. hold. on. hold on.
Who shot you?

560
00:24:06.962 --> 00:24:08.062
What?

561
00:24:08.096 --> 00:24:09.997
Your story was.
you caught a stray

562
00:24:10.032 --> 00:24:11.732
walking through Ellwood Park.

563
00:24:11.767 --> 00:24:13.635
But. now.
that's not true. is it?

564
00:24:13.669 --> 00:24:16.070
Not if you
"took a bullet for your troubles."

565
00:24:16.104 --> 00:24:18.104
It was Agent Keen. wasn't it?

566
00:24:18.139 --> 00:24:20.366
Yo. I never said that.

567
00:24:20.389 --> 00:24:22.033
Mm-hmm.

568
00:24:22.057 --> 00:24:24.878
Get a forensic unit to comb over
every inch of that ship.

569
00:24:24.912 --> 00:24:26.547
Tell them to tear up the floor

570
00:24:26.581 --> 00:24:28.182
until they hit water
if they have to.

571
00:24:28.216 --> 00:24:29.749
If there's a shell casing
or a stray bullet.

572
00:24:29.784 --> 00:24:30.817
I want it found.

573
00:24:37.157 --> 00:24:38.924
[ Off-key ]
♪ dancin' in the moonlight

574
00:24:38.958 --> 00:24:42.395
♪ everybody's feelin'
warm and bright ♪

575
00:24:42.429 --> 00:24:45.198
♪ it's such a fine
and natural sight ♪

576
00:24:48.402 --> 00:24:51.403
[ Engine revving ]

577
00:24:51.437 --> 00:24:53.638
♪ It's such a fine
and natural ♪

578
00:24:53.673 --> 00:24:55.139
[ Silenced gunshot ]

579
00:24:55.174 --> 00:24:57.309
♪ <i>Everybody's dancin'</i>
<i>in the moonlight</i> ♪

580
00:24:57.343 --> 00:24:58.677
[ Engine revs ]

581
00:24:58.711 --> 00:25:00.812
♪ <i>We like our fun.</i>
<i>and we never fight</i> ♪

582
00:25:00.846 --> 00:25:03.381
♪ <i>you can't dance</i>
<i>and stay uptight</i> ♪

583
00:25:03.416 --> 00:25:04.482
♪ <i>it's a supernatural deligh</i>♪

584
00:25:04.517 --> 00:25:06.784
[ Horn blares ]

585
00:25:06.819 --> 00:25:10.221
♪ <i>Everybody was dancin'</i>
<i>in the...</i> ♪

586
00:25:11.028 --> 00:25:13.023
You know.
I've never been in a situation like this.

587
00:25:13.057 --> 00:25:14.458
I'm being asked to prevent

588
00:25:14.492 --> 00:25:16.960
a murder investigation
from moving forward...

589
00:25:16.994 --> 00:25:18.795
The murder of a cop. no less...

590
00:25:18.830 --> 00:25:21.699
Based on the grounds that
what you do is so important

591
00:25:21.733 --> 00:25:23.133
it needs to be kept secret

592
00:25:23.167 --> 00:25:25.968
in the name
of national security.

593
00:25:26.002 --> 00:25:29.239
Tell me why you think
I should do that.

594
00:25:29.273 --> 00:25:32.141
Why will our democracy crumble
if the world knows about

595
00:25:32.175 --> 00:25:34.244
the inner workings
of this task force?

596
00:25:34.278 --> 00:25:37.004
It won't. but people will die.

597
00:25:37.016 --> 00:25:38.813
They already have.

598
00:25:38.836 --> 00:25:41.924
The black site
where we operate from...

599
00:25:41.948 --> 00:25:43.084
There was an incursion.

600
00:25:43.119 --> 00:25:44.152
[ Explosion ]

601
00:25:44.186 --> 00:25:46.388
[ Gunfire ]

602
00:25:47.490 --> 00:25:49.758
A mole leaked the information
about what we do.

603
00:25:49.781 --> 00:25:52.294
and as a result.
an extraction team was sent

604
00:25:52.328 --> 00:25:53.295
to abduct Reddington.

605
00:25:53.329 --> 00:25:55.029
He barricaded himself in.

606
00:25:55.064 --> 00:25:56.164
He wouldn't come out.

607
00:25:56.198 --> 00:25:57.366
and the team made good

608
00:25:57.400 --> 00:25:59.800
on their threat to kill
innocents until he did.

609
00:25:59.834 --> 00:26:01.201
[ Gunshot ]

610
00:26:01.236 --> 00:26:02.670
He just let people die?

611
00:26:02.704 --> 00:26:04.426
He didn't care who was killed?

612
00:26:04.450 --> 00:26:07.150
- Except one.
- Who?

613
00:26:07.174 --> 00:26:08.641
Me.

614
00:26:08.665 --> 00:26:11.612
He agreed to come out
when they put a gun to my head.

615
00:26:11.647 --> 00:26:13.147
After that.
Reddington vanished.

616
00:26:13.181 --> 00:26:15.115
He wouldn't come back
into the headquarters

617
00:26:15.150 --> 00:26:17.049
- until the mole was found.
- And who was it?

618
00:26:17.084 --> 00:26:20.186
We don't know for sure.
but Reddington only returned

619
00:26:20.220 --> 00:26:22.689
after the disappearance
of Diane Fowler.

620
00:26:22.723 --> 00:26:24.658
[ Gunshots ]

621
00:26:28.738 --> 00:26:30.397
Are you suggesting that
the former head

622
00:26:30.431 --> 00:26:34.333
of the Criminal Division
at Main Justice was a mole?

623
00:26:34.367 --> 00:26:36.802
- For whom?
- I don't know for sure.

624
00:26:40.676 --> 00:26:43.709
He let agents die. but not you.

625
00:26:43.743 --> 00:26:45.411
This man you're not
in league with.

626
00:26:45.445 --> 00:26:48.046
who's not your friend.

627
00:26:51.650 --> 00:26:54.185
You said before that
Reddington had answers

628
00:26:54.219 --> 00:26:56.587
to questions you
hadn't even thought of.

629
00:26:56.622 --> 00:26:57.855
Has he given you any?

630
00:26:58.976 --> 00:27:05.920
Well... There was a time early on
when I thought.

631
00:27:05.944 --> 00:27:07.198
because of his implications.

632
00:27:07.232 --> 00:27:08.998
that he might be my father.

633
00:27:09.818 --> 00:27:11.370
You didn't know your father?

634
00:27:11.394 --> 00:27:15.205
No.
He died in a fire.

635
00:27:15.616 --> 00:27:18.107
And your mother?

636
00:27:18.142 --> 00:27:20.744
She died when I was young.

637
00:27:20.778 --> 00:27:25.214
The man who raised me.
my adoptive father.

638
00:27:25.248 --> 00:27:26.382
his name was Sam Milhoan.

639
00:27:26.416 --> 00:27:28.217
Does he have a connection
to Reddington?

640
00:27:28.251 --> 00:27:29.675
- Yes.
- What connection?

641
00:27:29.699 --> 00:27:30.786
I-I don't know.

642
00:27:30.821 --> 00:27:31.821
But they knew each other?

643
00:27:34.257 --> 00:27:36.353
[ Muffled shouting ]

644
00:27:36.377 --> 00:27:38.861
Yes. Reddington was there
when my father died.

645
00:27:38.895 --> 00:27:40.796
You've sat here and told me

646
00:27:40.831 --> 00:27:42.731
you had no relationship
with Reddington

647
00:27:42.765 --> 00:27:45.066
before he turned himself in.
and now you're telling me

648
00:27:45.100 --> 00:27:47.134
he was close enough to your father
to be with him when he died?

649
00:27:47.169 --> 00:27:48.202
I didn't say they were close.

650
00:27:48.237 --> 00:27:49.337
We're taking a break.

651
00:27:51.039 --> 00:27:52.774
Wait. why?

652
00:27:52.808 --> 00:27:54.476
You need to think long and hard

653
00:27:54.510 --> 00:27:56.444
about this story
that you're telling.

654
00:27:56.479 --> 00:27:58.379
It's not a <i>story</i>.
This is the truth.

655
00:27:58.413 --> 00:27:59.847
That the man you said
you'd never met.

656
00:27:59.881 --> 00:28:01.749
a notorious criminal.
had a mysterious relationship

657
00:28:01.783 --> 00:28:02.916
with the man who raised you?

658
00:28:02.950 --> 00:28:06.086
- Yes.
- Your dead husband was a spy.

659
00:28:06.120 --> 00:28:07.721
and you never knew
your parents.

660
00:28:07.756 --> 00:28:09.423
and no one's heard
of the criminals you hunt.

661
00:28:09.457 --> 00:28:12.125
and for some reason.
you claim not to know

662
00:28:12.159 --> 00:28:14.995
why you were chosen
to be at the center of it all.

663
00:28:16.764 --> 00:28:19.329
Wait! Wa... I don't...

664
00:28:19.353 --> 00:28:20.400
I don't want to take a break.

665
00:28:20.434 --> 00:28:22.417
I would like to finish
and go home.

666
00:28:24.805 --> 00:28:26.806
[ Door closes ]

667
00:28:30.677 --> 00:28:33.278
You want something
from the vending machine?

668
00:28:47.860 --> 00:28:49.960
This better be important.

669
00:28:51.482 --> 00:28:53.464
You know the rules.

670
00:28:54.218 --> 00:28:56.617
Once you're in. no contact.

671
00:28:57.732 --> 00:29:01.305
You said on the phone
that this was mission-critical.

672
00:29:01.707 --> 00:29:03.273
What's wrong?

673
00:29:03.914 --> 00:29:04.942
Oh.

674
00:29:04.976 --> 00:29:07.276
[ Guns cocking ]

675
00:29:07.311 --> 00:29:08.645
Hands.

676
00:29:13.984 --> 00:29:15.418
[ Door opens ]

677
00:29:21.949 --> 00:29:23.959
Reddington.

678
00:29:24.967 --> 00:29:26.752
What is this?

679
00:29:29.072 --> 00:29:30.693
What do you want?

680
00:29:31.491 --> 00:29:33.268
I want Tom Keen.

681
00:29:37.294 --> 00:29:39.594
Denner: You said
Reddington had a list.

682
00:29:39.629 --> 00:29:40.995
He calls it the Blacklist.

683
00:29:41.030 --> 00:29:42.063
And who maintains it?

684
00:29:42.097 --> 00:29:43.664
Does Harold Cooper
keep track of...

685
00:29:43.698 --> 00:29:45.098
There is no physical list.

686
00:29:45.133 --> 00:29:47.067
The names are all
in Reddington's head.

687
00:29:47.935 --> 00:29:49.169
So they're all random.

688
00:29:49.203 --> 00:29:50.738
No.
I-I don't believe so.

689
00:29:50.772 --> 00:29:52.670
I believe that each case.
each criminal

690
00:29:52.688 --> 00:29:54.689
is somehow part
of a larger agenda.

691
00:29:54.723 --> 00:29:55.690
What agenda?

692
00:29:55.724 --> 00:29:56.824
I can't be sure.

693
00:29:56.858 --> 00:29:58.593
but he always has an angle
for every case.

694
00:29:58.627 --> 00:29:59.860
I know that.

695
00:29:59.895 --> 00:30:02.996
So Reddington is using you
to expand his criminal empire.

696
00:30:03.030 --> 00:30:04.598
No. W-well. yes.

697
00:30:04.632 --> 00:30:06.200
And you're okay with all this?

698
00:30:06.234 --> 00:30:08.168
I wasn't at first.
but as it turns out.

699
00:30:08.203 --> 00:30:10.370
the cases he brings us
are far more valuable

700
00:30:10.405 --> 00:30:12.772
to national security
than what he gets in return.

701
00:30:12.807 --> 00:30:15.409
But Reddington still tailors
individual cases

702
00:30:15.443 --> 00:30:16.743
for his personal gain?

703
00:30:16.777 --> 00:30:19.112
They're not individual.
Some of them are connected.

704
00:30:19.146 --> 00:30:20.179
Connected how?

705
00:30:20.214 --> 00:30:21.614
Reddington got a number
from Wujing.

706
00:30:21.648 --> 00:30:24.049
a code that he entered
into VICAP

707
00:30:24.084 --> 00:30:26.552
after helping us stop
General Ludd

708
00:30:26.587 --> 00:30:29.188
in order to identify
Lucy Brooks.

709
00:30:29.223 --> 00:30:31.390
also known as Jolene Parker.

710
00:30:31.425 --> 00:30:35.427
who he then tracked down using
the Alchemist's client list.

711
00:30:35.461 --> 00:30:37.061
Gina Zanetakos. the Courier...

712
00:30:37.096 --> 00:30:41.199
I believe they all trace back
to one entity.

713
00:30:41.234 --> 00:30:44.202
At first. I thought the cases
were all about getting Berlin.

714
00:30:44.237 --> 00:30:45.570
The man
your husband worked for.

715
00:30:45.605 --> 00:30:46.904
And most of them were.

716
00:30:46.939 --> 00:30:49.107
And. yes. he's using us.
It's true.

717
00:30:49.142 --> 00:30:51.742
But in the process.
we've been able to capture

718
00:30:51.776 --> 00:30:55.179
and kill a number of high-value targets.
including Berlin.

719
00:30:55.213 --> 00:30:56.980
And I thought
that was the end game.

720
00:30:57.015 --> 00:31:00.451
but as it turns out.
Reddington has other agendas.

721
00:31:01.315 --> 00:31:03.320
And all of those
are connected somehow?

722
00:31:03.355 --> 00:31:05.989
I can't know for sure. but. yes.
I imagine they're connected.

723
00:31:06.560 --> 00:31:08.224
Like his recent arrest
in Hong Kong.

724
00:31:08.259 --> 00:31:09.659
The cover story.

725
00:31:09.693 --> 00:31:11.093
He wanted to be captured.

726
00:31:11.128 --> 00:31:12.595
It's all a part of his quest

727
00:31:12.630 --> 00:31:14.631
to find something he calls
"The Fulcrum."

728
00:31:15.284 --> 00:31:15.998
The Fulcrum.

729
00:31:16.033 --> 00:31:17.233
It's a blackmail file.

730
00:31:17.268 --> 00:31:19.302
And before you decide
whether or not

731
00:31:19.336 --> 00:31:21.471
to discuss what we know
in open court.

732
00:31:21.505 --> 00:31:23.406
you should know that.
according to Reddington.

733
00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:25.574
the Fulcrum
is proof of the existence

734
00:31:25.608 --> 00:31:27.409
of a clandestine organization.

735
00:31:27.443 --> 00:31:29.711
and if its activities
were made public.

736
00:31:29.745 --> 00:31:32.347
a number
of very powerful people

737
00:31:32.382 --> 00:31:33.748
would go to prison
or be executed.

738
00:31:33.783 --> 00:31:35.150
You say that
like it's a bad thing.

739
00:31:35.185 --> 00:31:37.986
We don't know if
what Reddington alleges is true.

740
00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:40.422
and until we can confirm
his allegations.

741
00:31:40.456 --> 00:31:41.823
until we find the proof.

742
00:31:41.857 --> 00:31:43.791
the only people
who would benefit

743
00:31:43.825 --> 00:31:45.726
from the Fulcrum
being publicized

744
00:31:45.760 --> 00:31:47.461
are the criminals
it identifies.

745
00:31:47.496 --> 00:31:53.033
So. Hong Kong...
Did Reddington find this Fulcrum?

746
00:31:53.068 --> 00:31:54.554
No.

747
00:31:54.578 --> 00:31:58.034
And does he have some other
ideas about how to locate it?

748
00:31:58.068 --> 00:31:59.801
Yes... Through me.

749
00:31:59.836 --> 00:32:00.969
You?

750
00:32:01.004 --> 00:32:02.971
That's what I've come
to believe

751
00:32:03.006 --> 00:32:05.240
is the real reason he
surrendered in the first place.

752
00:32:05.274 --> 00:32:06.775
- asked for me.
- And let me guess...

753
00:32:06.809 --> 00:32:09.044
This comes as
a complete surprise to you.

754
00:32:09.078 --> 00:32:10.278
Absolutely.

755
00:32:10.312 --> 00:32:12.648
The same way
you were completely surprised

756
00:32:12.682 --> 00:32:13.682
when he asked for you.

757
00:32:13.716 --> 00:32:14.917
Yes.

758
00:32:14.951 --> 00:32:18.152
And the way you found out
that your husband was a spy.

759
00:32:18.186 --> 00:32:20.220
I'm sorry. You're right.
You're absolutely right.

760
00:32:20.255 --> 00:32:21.455
I should have known

761
00:32:21.489 --> 00:32:23.057
that when my husband and I
were planning family

762
00:32:23.091 --> 00:32:24.892
that he was. in fact. a traitor

763
00:32:24.927 --> 00:32:27.628
who had installed surveillance
cameras in my bedroom!

764
00:32:27.663 --> 00:32:29.564
Of course
I should have been aware

765
00:32:29.598 --> 00:32:32.232
that the number four
on the FBI's most wanted list

766
00:32:32.267 --> 00:32:35.435
would turn himself in
and demand to speak only to me!

767
00:32:35.469 --> 00:32:38.104
God.
what a horrible profiler I must be

768
00:32:38.138 --> 00:32:40.874
to have missed the fact
that I am central

769
00:32:40.908 --> 00:32:43.376
to the discovery
of a blackmail file

770
00:32:43.410 --> 00:32:46.112
that will tilt
the balance of power in...

771
00:32:46.146 --> 00:32:50.783
Let me phrase this right...
The entire world!

772
00:32:50.817 --> 00:32:53.018
Wow! I suck!

773
00:33:01.194 --> 00:33:03.062
[ Drawer opens. closes ]

774
00:33:03.096 --> 00:33:04.964
I think we've gotten
a little off topic.

775
00:33:06.611 --> 00:33:08.365
Regarding Mr. Ames.

776
00:33:09.112 --> 00:33:11.669
according to Detective Wilcox.

777
00:33:11.704 --> 00:33:14.138
you said that you were
on official business

778
00:33:14.172 --> 00:33:17.075
when you encountered Mr. Ames
on the ship the <i>Phoenix</i>.

779
00:33:17.109 --> 00:33:19.944
As I told the detective.
I was there looking for a fugitive.

780
00:33:19.979 --> 00:33:21.779
<i>Fugitives</i>...
From Cumberland.

781
00:33:21.814 --> 00:33:23.748
FBI.
We're searching for two fugitives

782
00:33:23.782 --> 00:33:25.782
escaped from Cumberland
last night.

783
00:33:25.817 --> 00:33:27.684
I never said Cumberland.

784
00:33:27.719 --> 00:33:30.087
and I was only looking for one man...
Samuel Aleko.

785
00:33:30.121 --> 00:33:31.922
He had a warrant out
for his arrest.

786
00:33:31.956 --> 00:33:33.189
and I had reason to believe

787
00:33:33.224 --> 00:33:35.092
that he was hiding out
on the <i>Phoenix</i>.

788
00:33:35.126 --> 00:33:37.160
In what way
is Mr. Aleko connected

789
00:33:37.194 --> 00:33:39.295
to the business
of your task force?

790
00:33:39.330 --> 00:33:41.564
He had been an informant
for a colleague of mine

791
00:33:41.599 --> 00:33:46.002
who was killed in the line of duty...
Meera Malik.

792
00:33:46.036 --> 00:33:48.437
I was hoping
I could cut a deal with Aleko

793
00:33:48.471 --> 00:33:49.939
and have him inform for me.

794
00:33:49.973 --> 00:33:51.573
Mr. Aleko says
you're lying.

795
00:33:51.608 --> 00:33:53.275
- In his statement...
- Which he recanted.

796
00:33:53.309 --> 00:33:55.711
He says that you kept
your ex-husband hostage

797
00:33:55.746 --> 00:33:57.379
on the <i>Phoenix</i> for four months

798
00:33:57.413 --> 00:33:59.648
- and that you interrogated him there.
- That's not true.

799
00:33:59.682 --> 00:34:02.117
How often did you communicate
with Berlin?

800
00:34:02.151 --> 00:34:03.384
- I want a name.
- My name is Jacob Phelps.

801
00:34:03.418 --> 00:34:04.653
Did you murder Jolene Parker?
Why you?

802
00:34:04.687 --> 00:34:05.820
Have you spied on others?
Is this...

803
00:34:05.855 --> 00:34:06.955
What do you know
about Reddington?

804
00:34:06.989 --> 00:34:08.222
What do you know
about Reddington?

805
00:34:08.257 --> 00:34:10.591
And when Mr. Ames found out
what you were doing.

806
00:34:10.626 --> 00:34:12.459
you and your husband
conspired to kill him.

807
00:34:12.483 --> 00:34:13.479
[ Chains clanking ]
No!

808
00:34:13.514 --> 00:34:15.280
[ Man gagging ]
It's better this way. Let him do it.

809
00:34:15.314 --> 00:34:17.149
Get off me!
Get your hands off me!

810
00:34:17.183 --> 00:34:18.250
Tom. stop!

811
00:34:20.085 --> 00:34:22.720
As I told you.
my ex-husband is dead.

812
00:34:22.755 --> 00:34:24.322
Perhaps I should remind you
that you're under oath.

813
00:34:24.357 --> 00:34:25.723
Perhaps I should remind <i>you</i>

814
00:34:25.758 --> 00:34:28.059
that the only evidence
against me is circumstantial.

815
00:34:28.093 --> 00:34:29.461
So it's your word against his?

816
00:34:29.495 --> 00:34:32.663
If I were holding my ex-husband
hostage and Mr. Ames found him.

817
00:34:32.697 --> 00:34:34.831
the last thing Tom would do
is kill him.

818
00:34:34.866 --> 00:34:38.101
the one man who could alert the
authorities and set him free.

819
00:34:38.136 --> 00:34:39.203
It makes no sense.

820
00:34:39.237 --> 00:34:41.071
Yes. it's my word against his.

821
00:34:42.140 --> 00:34:43.479
Not entirely.

822
00:34:45.498 --> 00:34:47.130
Okay. Send him in.

823
00:34:49.957 --> 00:34:52.315
I'm going to check your story
out with your boss.

824
00:34:52.349 --> 00:34:54.917
Good. I have no doubt
that Deputy Director Cooper

825
00:34:54.951 --> 00:34:56.286
will confirm my accounts.

826
00:34:56.320 --> 00:34:57.953
Well.
we should know soon enough.

827
00:34:57.988 --> 00:34:59.765
Mr. Cooper is right outside.

828
00:35:04.874 --> 00:35:07.894
For the moment. Agent Keen.
I think we're finished.

829
00:35:15.697 --> 00:35:17.458
Director Cooper. if you will.

830
00:35:19.842 --> 00:35:22.578
Look. I told you what happened
with Tom Keen.

831
00:35:23.086 --> 00:35:24.308
This is not my fault.

832
00:35:24.342 --> 00:35:26.644
You vouched for him personally.
Bill.

833
00:35:26.679 --> 00:35:30.014
I hired him
on your recommendation.

834
00:35:30.535 --> 00:35:32.383
The merchandise was defective.

835
00:35:32.417 --> 00:35:33.585
No.

836
00:35:33.619 --> 00:35:37.855
Keen was perfect...
Test scores. aptitude.

837
00:35:38.285 --> 00:35:41.592
There was no indication he would
become emotionally involved.

838
00:35:41.626 --> 00:35:43.426
But he did.

839
00:35:43.461 --> 00:35:44.661
He hasn't been in contact.

840
00:35:44.696 --> 00:35:46.697
Cut the crap. Bill.

841
00:35:46.731 --> 00:35:49.666
You acquired Tom Keen
when he was a boy.

842
00:35:49.701 --> 00:35:52.235
You trained him to be
a deep-cover operative.

843
00:35:52.269 --> 00:35:53.637
It's all he's ever done.

844
00:35:53.671 --> 00:35:56.206
It's all he knows.

845
00:35:56.240 --> 00:35:58.007
When one operation ends.

846
00:35:58.041 --> 00:36:00.409
he comes back to you
for another.

847
00:36:00.443 --> 00:36:01.543
Not this time.

848
00:36:03.714 --> 00:36:06.716
Mamat and I have come to
something of an understanding.

849
00:36:06.750 --> 00:36:10.920
He gets to remain alive and well.
still Deputy Minister.

850
00:36:10.954 --> 00:36:12.354
and I get you.

851
00:36:21.324 --> 00:36:22.964
I'm equally hopeful you and I

852
00:36:22.999 --> 00:36:25.967
can arrive at a mutually
beneficial solution.

853
00:36:26.002 --> 00:36:28.536
Even if I knew where he was.
I wouldn't tell you.

854
00:36:28.570 --> 00:36:32.439
Keen's betrayal cost me dearly

855
00:36:32.473 --> 00:36:37.011
in time. money. lives.

856
00:36:37.045 --> 00:36:40.547
Some of the people closest to me
are now dead

857
00:36:40.581 --> 00:36:41.915
because of Tom Keen.

858
00:36:41.950 --> 00:36:46.053
If I gave you his location.
I'd have to betray a client.

859
00:36:46.087 --> 00:36:48.888
That shouldn't be hard. Bill.

860
00:36:48.922 --> 00:36:50.623
You betrayed <i>me</i>.

861
00:36:52.826 --> 00:36:55.995
You sold me an asset
and then allowed him to turn

862
00:36:56.030 --> 00:36:58.597
when Berlin offered you
twice as much.

863
00:36:58.632 --> 00:37:01.934
You're in debt to me.

864
00:37:01.969 --> 00:37:05.337
Recognize this
rather fortuitous opportunity

865
00:37:05.372 --> 00:37:08.306
for you to begin
to make things even.

866
00:37:10.209 --> 00:37:12.443
Where can I find Tom Keen?

867
00:37:18.883 --> 00:37:20.992
Denner: I have been listening
to Elizabeth Keen

868
00:37:21.027 --> 00:37:23.161
describe the work
of your task force.

869
00:37:23.196 --> 00:37:24.630
and I have many questions.

870
00:37:24.664 --> 00:37:27.366
but it's safe to say there's
only one I need to put to you.

871
00:37:27.400 --> 00:37:30.168
and that question is.
as her boss.

872
00:37:30.203 --> 00:37:35.207
can you tell me if Agent Keen
was on that boat. the <i>Phoenix</i>.

873
00:37:35.241 --> 00:37:37.742
in her official capacity
as an FBI agent.

874
00:37:37.776 --> 00:37:40.762
or was she there.
as appears far more likely to me.

875
00:37:40.785 --> 00:37:42.613
for personal reasons
that had nothing to do

876
00:37:42.648 --> 00:37:45.216
with the work of your task force
and the FBI?

877
00:37:45.250 --> 00:37:47.117
I understand you need
to ask me the question.

878
00:37:47.152 --> 00:37:48.619
but I assume
it's only to confirm

879
00:37:48.654 --> 00:37:50.321
what Agent Keen
has already told you...

880
00:37:50.356 --> 00:37:51.823
That she has addressed this

881
00:37:51.857 --> 00:37:54.758
and eliminated any need
for me to testify under oath.

882
00:37:54.792 --> 00:37:56.960
No.

883
00:37:56.994 --> 00:38:00.296
Agent Keen put you
directly on the hot seat.

884
00:38:00.331 --> 00:38:05.068
She not only said that she
was there on official business.

885
00:38:05.102 --> 00:38:06.870
she specifically said
on the record

886
00:38:06.904 --> 00:38:08.204
that you would confirm this.

887
00:38:08.239 --> 00:38:10.173
Now. I know this must
be difficult for you.

888
00:38:10.207 --> 00:38:11.640
Agent Keen is one of your own.

889
00:38:11.675 --> 00:38:13.509
and your instinct
is to be loyal to her.

890
00:38:13.543 --> 00:38:15.511
But she put herself
in this position.

891
00:38:15.545 --> 00:38:17.980
and I strongly advise you
to not commit perjury

892
00:38:18.014 --> 00:38:19.548
- to protect her from...
- Yes.

893
00:38:21.489 --> 00:38:22.769
Yes. what?

894
00:38:23.473 --> 00:38:26.321
Yes. Agent Keen was on that ship.
the <i>Phoenix</i>.

895
00:38:26.356 --> 00:38:29.991
as part of the official duties
of our task force.

896
00:38:32.294 --> 00:38:35.563
You're walking down a very
dangerous road here. Director.

897
00:38:36.448 --> 00:38:38.332
You understand that
if you perjure yourself...

898
00:38:38.367 --> 00:38:40.735
You asked me a question.
and I answered it.

899
00:38:40.770 --> 00:38:41.870
Are we finished?

900
00:38:41.904 --> 00:38:43.705
I can push you for specifics.

901
00:38:43.739 --> 00:38:45.572
As I understand it.
your job is to determine

902
00:38:45.607 --> 00:38:47.741
whether a grand jury
should go forward on this issue.

903
00:38:47.776 --> 00:38:49.476
Now. if you want
to put me before them.

904
00:38:49.511 --> 00:38:51.144
have me answer their questions.
fine.

905
00:38:51.178 --> 00:38:52.713
But I have answered
the one question

906
00:38:52.747 --> 00:38:55.315
you said you wanted me
to answer.

907
00:38:55.349 --> 00:38:57.017
So if there's nothing else...

908
00:39:03.364 --> 00:39:04.424
Director Cooper.

909
00:39:06.126 --> 00:39:08.961
Something tells me we will
be speaking again soon.

910
00:39:16.002 --> 00:39:17.603
[ Knock on door ]
What do you got?

911
00:39:17.638 --> 00:39:19.741
- Let me see it.
- Found it lodged in the ship's hull.

912
00:39:19.765 --> 00:39:21.397
There it is.

913
00:39:21.420 --> 00:39:23.975
Have ballistics run it against
Agent Keen's service weapon.

914
00:39:24.009 --> 00:39:25.610
- She surrendered it when she
entered the courthouse. - Got it.

915
00:39:25.645 --> 00:39:26.778
Have the lab process the blood

916
00:39:26.813 --> 00:39:29.047
to look for a DNA match
to Aleko.

917
00:39:29.081 --> 00:39:31.149
I'm gonna need results fast.

918
00:39:31.183 --> 00:39:33.151
Man: Yes. sir.

919
00:39:36.555 --> 00:39:38.322
[ German metal music playing ]

920
00:39:41.634 --> 00:39:43.184
_

921
00:39:45.885 --> 00:39:47.928
_

922
00:39:52.766 --> 00:39:54.283
_

923
00:39:54.306 --> 00:39:58.216
_

924
00:39:58.239 --> 00:39:59.977
_

925
00:40:00.001 --> 00:40:02.180
_

926
00:40:02.204 --> 00:40:05.186
_

927
00:40:05.210 --> 00:40:07.687
_

928
00:40:10.493 --> 00:40:12.830
_

929
00:40:15.892 --> 00:40:18.727
Red: Well. that went as well
as could be expected.

930
00:40:18.761 --> 00:40:19.995
We got a lead on Keen

931
00:40:20.029 --> 00:40:22.664
and an invitation
to sit in the Minister's box

932
00:40:22.699 --> 00:40:24.332
at next year's Slasher Cup.

933
00:40:24.367 --> 00:40:26.868
Cultural peculiarities
notwithstanding.

934
00:40:26.902 --> 00:40:29.704
I find cockfighting
to be abominable.

935
00:40:29.738 --> 00:40:33.908
However. truth be told.
I do love fried chicken.

936
00:40:33.942 --> 00:40:35.510
You need to tell her. Raymond.

937
00:40:38.580 --> 00:40:39.580
Tell her what?

938
00:40:39.615 --> 00:40:41.415
About Tom.

939
00:40:41.449 --> 00:40:44.083
You should have told her
some time ago.

940
00:40:45.101 --> 00:40:46.953
I don't know how do that.
Dembe.

941
00:40:46.988 --> 00:40:48.755
Yes. you do.

942
00:40:48.789 --> 00:40:51.525
You tell her the truth
by telling her everything.

943
00:40:57.698 --> 00:40:59.733
I don't think I can do that.

944
00:41:01.668 --> 00:41:04.737
Maybe you should stop
thinking about it and do it.

945
00:41:09.375 --> 00:41:11.010
Sorry to interrupt. Your Honor.

946
00:41:11.044 --> 00:41:12.711
- This couldn't wait.
- What am I looking at?

947
00:41:12.746 --> 00:41:15.180
A discharged bullet
found at the scene.

948
00:41:15.214 --> 00:41:17.449
It's a match
to Agent Keen's firearm.

949
00:41:17.483 --> 00:41:19.116
Trace amounts
of Samuel Aleko's blood

950
00:41:19.151 --> 00:41:21.052
were found on the casing.

951
00:41:21.086 --> 00:41:22.854
- When did you find this?
- Wilcox: Five hours ago.

952
00:41:22.888 --> 00:41:25.122
Your Honor. this is...
This is direct physical evidence

953
00:41:25.157 --> 00:41:26.624
that Agent Keen
lied to the court.

954
00:41:26.659 --> 00:41:29.093
She says that she never saw
Mr. Aleko on that ship.

955
00:41:29.127 --> 00:41:30.461
but that can't be reconciled

956
00:41:30.495 --> 00:41:32.730
with the fact that a bullet
fired from her gun

957
00:41:32.765 --> 00:41:34.365
passed through
Mr. Aleko's body

958
00:41:34.399 --> 00:41:36.132
and was found on the ship
with his blood on it.

959
00:41:36.167 --> 00:41:38.936
It's proof that she's trying to
cover up the truth. Your Honor.

960
00:41:38.970 --> 00:41:40.604
and the truth

961
00:41:40.638 --> 00:41:43.139
is that Elizabeth Keen
killed Eugene Ames.

962
00:41:43.259 --> 00:41:45.974
Sync. corrected by icephoenix
www.addic7ed.com

